page_title: 'Quickstart: Use Azure OpenAI Service with the Java SDK'
page_description: Walkthrough on how to get started with Azure OpenAI and make your first chat completions call with the Java SDK.
chunk_content: Install the Java SDKThis quickstart uses the Gradle dependency manager. You can find the client library and information for other dependency managers on the Maven Central Repository.Locate *build.gradle.kts* and open it with your preferred IDE or text editor. Then copy in the following build configuration. This configuration defines the project as a Java application whose entry point is the class OpenAIQuickstart. It imports the Azure AI Vision library.```kotlinplugins {    java    application}application {     mainClass.set("OpenAIQuickstart")}repositories {    mavenCentral()}dependencies {    implementation(group = "com.azure", name = "azure-ai-openai", version = "1.0.0-beta.10")    implementation("org.slf4j:slf4j-simple:1.7.9")}```
